  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is a move to &quot;scarless surgery&quot; and this achieved by doing laparoscopic abdominal
      surgery though a single small umbilical incision. A technique for laparoscopic appendectomy
      done through a single incision utilizing conventional instruments has been developed. The
      operative risk of the single incision approach is no different that the standard three
      incision laparoscopic appendectomy. The goal is to study the operative time, length of
      hospital stay, and complications from this operation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
